claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: Table presenting percentages of local (pain, redness, swelling, bruising) and systemic (headache, fatigue, muscle pain, nausea, joint pain, chills, fever) adverse events in two groups: Flublok (N=2272) and placebo (N=2231). does not support the claim because the table only reports adverse event rates for Flublok versus placebo and contains no information on cell- or egg-based vaccine production, mutations, or their impact on effectiveness
